text_blocks.content: 1 Instruction No. 16: Count Two: Enticement to Engage in Illegal Sexual Activity - Second Element

The second element of Count Two which the Government must prove beyond a reasonable doubt is that the individual traveled in interstate commerce, as alleged in the Indictment. As I just stated, "interstate commerce" simply means movement between one state and another.
